### Custom Textarea Field Label Server Component (React/TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/textarea.mdx

This snippet defines a custom server component for rendering the label of a Textarea Field. It uses React and TypeScript, importing 'FieldLabel' from '@payloadcms/ui'. The component displays the field's label or name and indicates if it's required, ensuring consistent label presentation.

```tsx
import React from 'react'
import { FieldLabel } from '@payloadcms/ui'
import type { TextareaFieldLabelServerComponent } from 'payload'

export const CustomTextareaFieldLabelServer: TextareaFieldLabelServerComponent =
  ({ clientField, path }) => {
    return (
      <FieldLabel
        label={clientField?.label || clientField?.name}
        path={path}
        required={clientField?.required}
      />
    )
  }

```

