### Define Payload CMS Tabs Field for Content Organization

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/FIELDS.md

Creates a 'tabs' field to organize related fields into distinct tabbed sections within the Payload CMS admin. The example defines 'Content' and 'SEO' tabs, each containing relevant input fields like text areas and rich text editors.

```ts
import type { TabsField, GroupField } from 'payload'

// Tabs
const tabsField: TabsField = {
  type: 'tabs',
  tabs: [
    {
      label: 'Content',
      fields: [
        { name: 'title', type: 'text' },
        { name: 'body', type: 'richText' },
      ],
    },
    {
      label: 'SEO',
      fields: [
        { name: 'metaTitle', type: 'text' },
        { name: 'metaDescription', type: 'textarea' },
      ],
    },
  ],
}
```

