### Override Payload CMS Slug Field Default Configuration (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/fields/text.mdx

This TypeScript code illustrates how to customize the default configuration of a Payload CMS slug field using the `overrides` function. It allows granular modification of the slug field's internal structure, such as changing a sub-field's label, by receiving and returning the default field configuration.

```ts
import { slugField } from 'payload'
import type { CollectionConfig } from 'payload'

export const ExampleCollection: CollectionConfig = {
  // ...
  fields: [
    // ...
    // highlight-line
    slugField({
      overrides: (defaultField) => {
        defaultField.fields[1].label = 'Custom Slug Label'
        return defaultField
      },
    }),
    // highlight-line
  ],
}
```

